            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Deae Eponae <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arcus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>A</abbr><ex cert="low">urelius</ex></expan> <supplied reason="lost">Ap</supplied><lb break="no" n="2"/>rilius Restio m<supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>il</abbr><ex>es</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>leg</abbr><ex>ionis</ex></expan> XXII Antoni<supplied reason="lost">ni</supplied><lb break="no" n="4"/>anae <expan><abbr>P</abbr><ex>rimigeniae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>iae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>idelis</ex></expan> immu<supplied reason="lost">n</supplied><lb break="no" n="5"/>is co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ularis</ex></expan> curas a<supplied reason="lost">ge</supplied><lb break="no" n="6"/>ns vico Salod<supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>ur</abbr><ex>o</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="7"/>XIII <expan><abbr>Kal</abbr><ex>endas</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Septem</abbr><ex>bres</ex></expan> I<supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>mp</abbr><ex>eratore</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="8"/><expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>omino</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>n</abbr><ex>ostro</ex></expan> Antonino <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usto</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="9"/>II et Sacerdo<supplied reason="lost">te</supplied> <lb n="10"/>II co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ulibus</ex></expan> <lb n="11"/><expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>otum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>olvit</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>aetus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>ibens</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>erito</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Die vordere rechte Kante des Schaftes wurde für die Sekundärverwendung als Baumaterial im spätantiken Kastell schräg abgerbeitet. Inschriftfeld stellenweise ausgebrochen und bestoßen. Linker Rand des Inschriftfeldes erhalten. Die Buchstaben sind modern mit roter Farbe ausgemalt worden. (B): CIL 13, 05170: Z. 1/2: MA / [Po]pilius; ILS: Z. 1/2: ma[tri?] . . pilius; Walser: Z. 1/2: Ma[ga]/pilius; Kakoschke; Bartels u. a., MH 74, 2017: Z. 2: m[iles]; CIL 13, 05170; ILS; Walser: Z. 3: [l]eg(ionis); CIL 13, 05170; ILS: Z. 4/5: immu/[ni]s co(n)s(ularis); Walser: Z. 4/5: immu[n/i]s; CIL 13, 05170; ILS: Z. 5/6: a/[ge]ns; CIL 13, 05170; Walser: Z. 7: [d(ie)] XIII; CIL 13, 05170; ILS: Z. 7: Septemb(res) /; Walser: Septemb[r(es)] /.</p>
            </div>
